      "code": "M15-F-VCG01",
      "label": "Inner deliberative reasoning and questioning (dialogizomai/dialogismos)",
      "context_description": "The term names inner deliberative reasoning — questioning in the heart, calculating political consequences, reasoning within oneself in an interior monologue, and the evil thoughts that arise from the heart and produce sinful action. Jesus regularly perceives and names this inner deliberating; the dialogismos of the heart is the site of both corrupt reasoning and honest questioning. Inner-being phenomenon: inner deliberative reasoning.",
