    {
      "code": "M15-F-VCG02",
      "label": "Inner reflection and conceived thought (enthumeomai/enthumēsis)",
      "context_description": "The term names sustained inner reflection that produces conceived thoughts — Joseph contemplating his situation before the angel appears, Peter pondering the vision before the Spirit speaks, the Pharisees thinking evil in their hearts, and the formed inner thoughts that the word of God discerns. The phenomenon is the inner conceiving activity that generates thought-content. Inner-being phenomenon: inner reflective conceiving of thought.",
