        "reference": "Heb 4:12",
        "strongs": "G1761",
        "translit": "enthumēsis",
        "anchor_rationale": "'Discerning the thoughts and intentions of the heart.' The word of God penetrates to the enthumēseis (conceived thoughts) and intentions of the heart. This verse names the phenomenon directly: the thoughts that are conceived in the heart are the inner realities that the living word reaches. The dynamic (word penetrating to conceived thoughts) reveals what the term names — formed inner conceptions."
