      "anchor_proposed": {
        "vr_id": 181404,
        "reference": "Psa 119:97",
        "strongs": "H7881",
        "translit": "si.chah",
        "anchor_rationale": "'Oh how I love your law! It is my meditation all the day.' Love for the law finds its expression and sustaining in si.chah — all-day meditative dwelling on what God has said. The verse names the object (the law), the quality (all-day continuousness), and the relational tone (love) of meditative dwelling. No other verse states the phenomenon so fully."
      }
