    {
      "code": "M15-F-VCG04",
      "label": "Contemplation in vision and divine knowledge of human thought",
      "context_description": "The term names either Daniel's focused contemplative attention directed at the revelatory vision (se.khal), or the divine knowing and declaring of what is in the creature's thought (se.ach in Amos 4:13). The phenomenon is either the intense contemplative attending of the person in a revelatory context, or the divine penetrating awareness of human inner thought. Inner-being phenomenon: concentrated contemplation or divine attending to inner thought.",
